latestIgtvVideos.title: Om Namah Shivaya! I honor the divinity that resides within me!
latestIgtvVideos.caption: Practice with a gentle and humble heart. It’s your time to connect with your inner self. The self that knows everything, that has all the answers you are seeking. The self that knows only love and kindness. The self that tries to protect you from unwanted and unhealthy actions. The more time you spend knowing your real self, thru yoga (on the mat or off), thru through meditation, or other ways the better human you’ll turn into.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Home workout 3! Yoga during Menstruation!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A simple yoga flow that women can perform during menstruation. These asanas will help relieve any menstrual pain, cramps and will relax your mind. I recorded the video after my practice to simplify it for you all. 
Play some soothing music and practice ❤️ Stay safe 💛

latestIgtvVideos.title: Home Workout 2!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today’s workout
On the spot jogging for 2 mins

4 rounds of 
1. Wide hand push-ups: 10
2. Mountain Climbers: 80+ (total)
3. Wall sit: 1 min ( this will burn your legs)
4. Sit-ups: 10
5. Air squats: 20
Some yoga in the end 💛

Try it if you feel like working out at home! Let me know if you do❤️
You can modify as per your fitness level.

PS. except Push ups, the other workouts have been sped up

Audio: Aghori by @gurbaxx

latestIgtvVideos.title: Home Workout 1
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Did 5 rounds of the following workout followed by some Yoga asanas and 5000 steps

1. Plank - 1 min
2. Air Squats - 10
3. Lunges - 10 each side
4. Push-ups - 10
5. Knees to Chest - 10
6. Pike Push-ups - 10

30 sec breather between rounds! 
Audio: Boom Shankar by @gurbaxx

latestIgtvVideos.title: We are stronger than we seem ❤️ Physically, Mentally & Emotionally
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Did a 6 min plank today, breaking my own record of 5 mins. 
#gettingbetter #gettingthere 
Life is not easy.. but wake up every morning with gratitude for all that you have & get ready to run farther than you did yesterday and fight harder than you did ever before. Coz we are stronger than we seem ❣️ There may not be a tomorrow (hard but true) so live life to your fullest abilities today.

latestPosts.caption:
Are you a new mother and don’t know how and where to start your fitness journey post delivery. You want someone to safely guide you towards a healthier and fitter you. Want to strengthen your body spl the back, the core, you want to feel better devoid of aches and pains. Want some calm amidst the chaos, want a deeper connection with self? 

Look no further and join my postnatal yoga batch to get started!
Next batch starting 18th September
Mon | Wed | Fri, 6 PM to 6:45 PM IST

DM for details and Register through link in bio

January 2025 Online Yoga Classes

1. Postnatal Batch ( Suitable for 6 weeks post vaginal and 8 weeks post c sec delivery )
2. Prenatal Batch ( Suitable for those in 2nd & 3rd Trimester)
3. Movement Batch ( Suitable for those with a minimum 3 months of Yoga Asana Practice experience )

Check the link in bio for more details and to book your spot in the upcoming batch

First times are always hard! 
Kudos to all mothers! Kudos to supporting family members and to the little ones for adapting so well ❤️❤️

In motherhood Exhaustion takes over, time feels impossible to find and before you know it, you’ve stopped prioritising yourself.

It’s tough to fight the mind when it’s pulling you down but pushing back even just a little makes you stronger

Even the tiniest act of love and care can make a difference! 
If you’ve been waiting for a sign to begin, let this be it

Show up for yourself!

Living the moment we manifested three and a half years ago. Dreams, dedication, and a leap of faith has brought Sanyaas In the City to life.

Palatable excitement in peace...at the book launch in Mumbai @crosswordbookstores Kemps Corner

In order
1. The pillars of SITC in bliss
2. In the presence of luminaries @nawazbodyartmumbai @dr.mukeshbatra , @iradubey , Dr. Deepak Jumani and @hrishikay 
3. & 4. Moderating the fireside chat with us was the amazing @hrishikay elevating the conversation with his curious and thought provoking questions
5. Candid capture from the group discussion
6. 7. & 8. Candid moments captured signing the book
9. 10. & 11. Grateful to each one of you who joined us at the launch of Sanyaas In the City! Your presence, support, and curiosity to explore what SITC truly stands for mean the world to us. Thank you for being part of this special journey!
